The Federal Government has been called upon to take proactive measures against drug abuse by youths in northern Nigeria. This call was made by the President of a Non-Governmental Organization (NGO), Ungoggo Youth Active Ambassadors (UYAA), Umar Rabiâ€™u Muhammad in an interview with Daily Trust, in Abuja, yesterday. Muhammad who is a student at the department of Bio-Chemistry, Faculty of Life Science, ABU Zaria said drug abuse is destroying youths in the North. He said drug abuse has rendered youths in the region unproductive and vulnerable to committing crime.